UEFA have announced the date and location for both the Champions League and Europa League group stage draws. The draws and the handing of the 2019/20 awards will take place at their headquarters in Nyon, Switzerland, on October 1. Real Madrid, Barcelona, Atletico Madrid and Sevilla are the four LaLiga Santander teams which will participate in the Champions League draw. Villarreal and Real Sociedad have already secured qualification to the Europa League group stage, while Granada will have to progress through the qualifying rounds.